{
  "name": "Manipulate Healing",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "modules/pf1spheres/assets/icons/spheres/alteration.webp",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Alteration sphere (Vitality), caster level 10th.</p>\n<p>You may spend an additional spell point to add the following trait options to your forms:</p>\n<p><strong>Block Healing:</strong> You may remove any fast healing or regeneration the target possesses. Additionally, any attempt to magically heal the target requires a magical skill check against your MSD.</p>\n<p><strong>Regenerate Flesh:</strong> In addition to the normal healing from the Fast Healing option of the Vitality talent, the target&#8217;s severed body members (fingers, toes, hands, feet, arms, legs, tails, or even heads of multi-headed creatures), broken bones, and ruined organs grow back. The physical regeneration is complete in 1 round if the severed members are present and touching the creature. It takes 2d10 rounds otherwise. This is an upgrade to, and does not stack with, the Fast Healing trait.</p>\n",
